The paper deals with information gathering in ad-hoc radio networks, which is a topic related to networked systems and communication. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses tree topologies and algorithms, which are related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of acknowledgements and collision detection mechanisms is related to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI).
